Thought #TheGrayMan was way better than expected. Definitely the Russo's better non MCU movie. Gosling was badass in it and especially Ana De Armas. Some pretty dope action scenes. Although we've seen a lot of the stuff before, they still had some tidbits that felt fresh/new.

After the serviceable-ish #TheGrayMan (and the messy Cherry) from the Russo Bros, it’s hard not think about the films delivered by other directors *after* they made the highest grossing films at one point (Coppola, Spielberg, Cameron, etc). May not be fair to compare, but 🤷🏻‍♂️
